This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it deals with spectrum allocation for device-to-device communication. It also involves the use of deep reinforcement learning, which falls under the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper proposes a distributed framework, which involves multiple agents working together, making it relevant to the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper also involves information theory, making it relevant to the sub-category of Information Theory (cs.IT).
